data.description:
Location, Location, Location. A fixer uppers vision will transform this diamond in the rough. Your upgrades and sweat equity will greatly increase the worth of this home. Pleny of room for expansion along the back and one side of the house if you choose.  The surrounding houses will easily support any appreciated value you put into it.  It is currently very livable and has a new redesigned screened front porch  to enjoy the lake view, absolutely beautiful sunsets, watch the hummingbirds that come up to the porch and the eagle that flies over and lands in the nearby trees. The exterior of the home has been recently repainted, newly replaced hot water heater and new bathroom faucet/plumbing and toilet in half bath. Idlewilde sub division is the nicest well maintained neighborhood in Onalaska. Couple minutes from the boat ramp and fishing pier. Lots of wildlife and especially deer. The home is VA and FHA financeable. City water, sewer and gas.
Call owner Jerry Norris for an appointment to come and see or have your realtor call. 936-933-1405   jerrynorris22@yahoo.com
data.whatILove: Idlewilde is a beautiful neighborhood with friendly neighbors. I love sitting on my screened front porch in the morning as I pray and sip my morning coffee. The birds, squirrels and deer are an enjoyable pleasure for nature lovers and the humming birds are so adorable to watch. The evenings are especially beautiful since the home faces west and the sunsets are gorgeous and every few days you see a new sunset as the earth tilts on its natural axis. the neighborhood walks are a pleasure and the neighborhood is  safe for adults and children.
